<paragraph id="8BD2369B1C39FFABA3E8FAB4A239158B" blockId="11.[136,1452,1305,1907]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">
It differs from the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D181C39FFABA17AFAB4A3B21527" authorityName=", Am" authorityYear="1099" box="[538,730,1305,1331]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obliquum">
<emphasis id="B919EA891C39FFABA17AFAB4A3B21527" box="[538,730,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">Allium obliquum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by purple perianth (not yellow), falcate leaves (not oblique), hemispherical and lax inflorescence, rounded bulbs (not oblong ovate) with coriaceous tunics. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D181C39FFABA6F3FA90A076156F" authorityName="Redoute" authorityYear="1804" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carolinianum">
<emphasis id="B919EA891C39FFABA6F3FA90A076156F" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">A. carolinianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by inner filaments with obtuse teeth at the base (not triangular without teeth), and rounded (not ovoid), bulbs with dirty yellow coriaceous (not brown, leathery) tunics.
</paragraph>
